    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-10-07T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-10-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="625"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d625">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 711.0012/526.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Ambassador <persName type="to">Page</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 81.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-10-07">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 7, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department has received your No. 247 of the
                    15th ultimo and, referring to the last paragraph thereof, pointing out the
                    importance of the conclusion of a naturalization treaty between the United
                    States and Italy at the first opportunity, desires to say that it does not
                    regard the present as a favorable time to approach the Italian Government on the
                    subject of a naturalization treaty.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>For the Secretary of State: <lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
